                            <comment id="12510736" author="stack" created="Fri, 6 Jul 2007 16:51:02 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is a suggested patch.  It adds the hbase lib dir directly to the javadoc CLASSPATH in the root build.xml.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If folks have other suggestions for a solution, I&apos;m all ears.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12510772" author="cutting" created="Fri, 6 Jul 2007 19:56:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In general, this looks reasonable.  We might include all src/contrib/*/lib directories, so that other contrib modules won&apos;t have to make this change again if they add libraries.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12510773" author="stack" created="Fri, 6 Jul 2007 20:10:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the suggestion on how to generalize inclusion of libs D.  Attached is a slight varient on your suggestion &amp;#8211; one that doesn&apos;t complain about missing contrib lib dirs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12510798" author="stack" created="Fri, 6 Jul 2007 21:29:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Passes all tests locally.  Trying against hudson.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
